{"title_page": "Expo for Design, Innovation & Technology", "text_new": "{{Coord|43|38|48|N|79|23|25|W|display = title}}\n{{Infobox Film Festival\n| name            = Expo For Design, Innovation & Technology\n| logo            = \n| caption         =\n| image           = \n| image_alt       = \n| image_size      = \n| location        = [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n| website         = {{url|http://editdx.org/home}}\n}}\n\n'''Expo for Design, Innovation & Technology''' ('''EDIT''') is a 10-day festival launched by the [[Design Exchange]] (DX) in partnership with the [[United Nations Development Programme]] (UNDP). It is also supported by the [[Government of Ontario]] and its Ontario150 Program.<ref>[https://www.ontario.ca/page/ontario150/ Ontario 150]</ref> The festival has received a $1.75 million investment from the Government of Ontario in 2017.<ref>[https://torontoguardian.com/2017/05/edit-design-exchange/ A Game-Changing Festival of Innovation Hits Toronto this Fall]</ref> The festival focusses on design, innovation and technology solutions and highlights the potential that the design industry has to solve issues on a global scale. The first annual festival took place in Toronto from September 28 to October 8, 2017 with a capacity of approximately 100,000 visitors.\n\nThe overall theme to EDIT was \"Prosperity For All\". It was inspired by the United Nations Development Programme's (UNDP) Global Goals for Sustainable Development. The theme was portrayed through an art installation by designer Bruce Man, so cofounded Massive Change Network. It featured large black and white images of global conflict like pollution, genocide, and terrorism.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newswire.ca/news-releases/canada-makes-international-design-news-with-launch-of-edit-expo-for-design-innovation--technology-621214063.html|title=Canada Makes International Design News with Launch of EDIT: Expo for Design, Innovation & Technology|website=www.newswire.ca|language=en|access-date=2018-01-29}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category inline|Design Exchange}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20130726110913/http://www.dx.org/ Design Exchange]\n*[http://www.azuremagazine.com/article/bruce-mau-design-solutions-world-problems/ Bruce Mau on How Design Can Solve the World\u2019s Biggest Problems]\n*[http://www.azuremagazine.com/events/edit/ EDIT: Expo for Design, Innovation & Technology]\n*[https://www.canadianarchitect.com/events/edit-expo-design-innovation-technology/ EDIT I Expo for Design, Innovation and Technology]\n*[https://www.canadianinteriors.com/exhibition/dx-design-exchange-festival/1003740460/ Design Exchange launches 10-day biennial festival addressing global challenges]\n*[https://www.insidetoronto.com/news-story/7295479-edit-expo-brings-innovation-to-toronto-s-studio-district/ EDIT expo brings innovation to Toronto's Studio District]\n*[https://news.ontario.ca/mtc/en/2017/01/celebrate-ontarios-150th-anniversary-in-2017.html/ Celebrate Ontario's 150th Anniversary in 2017 Events Taking Place Across the Province Year-Round]\n*[https://nowtoronto.com/news/think-free-blog/prepare-to-party-at-the-old-unilever-soap-factory/ The old Unilever soap factory is open for business]\n*[http://nuvomagazine.com/design/edit-toronto/ EDIT TORONTO Canada\u2019s new immersive design festival.]\n*[https://passport2017.ca/events/edit-expo-design-innovation-technology/ EDIT: Expo for Design, Innovation & Technology]\n*[https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/art-and-architecture/torontos-edit-exhibition-strives-to-serve-global-goals-through-design/article34915374/ Toronto\u2019s EDIT exhibition strives to serve global goals through design]\n*[https://www.theglobeandmail.com/life/home-and-garden/design/bruce-maus-new-expo-to-highlight-how-design-can-save-us-fromourselves/article35160089/ The eternal optimist]\n*[https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/visualarts/2016/01/19/shauna-levy-raises-design-exchanges-capital.html/ Shauna Levy raises Design Exchange's capital]\n\n[[Category:Canadian design]]\n[[Category:Design events]]\n[[Category:2017 festivals in North America]]\n[[Category:Festivals in Toronto]]\n[[Category:150th anniversary of Canada]]\n[[Category:2017 in Toronto]]\n\n\n{{Toronto-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Coord|43|38|48|N|79|23|25|W|display = title}}\n{{Infobox Film Festival\n| name            = Expo For Design, Innovation & Technology\n| logo            = \n| caption         =\n| image           = \n| image_alt       = \n| image_size      = \n| location        = [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n| website         = {{url|http://editdx.org/home}}\n}}\n\n'''Expo for Design, Innovation & Technology''' ('''EDIT''') is a 10-day festival launched by the [[Design Exchange]] (DX) in partnership with the [[United Nations Development Programme]] (UNDP). It is also supported by the [[Government of Ontario]] and its Ontario150 Program.<ref>[https://www.ontario.ca/page/ontario150/ Ontario 150]</ref> The festival has received a $1.75 million investment from the Government of Ontario in 2017.<ref>[https://torontoguardian.com/2017/05/edit-design-exchange/ A Game-Changing Festival of Innovation Hits Toronto this Fall]</ref> The festival focusses on design, innovation and technology solutions and highlights the potential that the design industry has to solve issues on a global scale. The first annual festival took place in Toronto from September 28 to October 8, 2017 with a capacity of approximately 100,000 visitors.\n\nThe overall theme to EDIT was \"Prosperity For All\". It was inspired by the United Nations Development Programme's (UNDP) Global Goals for Sustainable Development. The theme was portrayed through an art installation by designer Bruce Man, so cofounded Massive Change Network. It featured large black and white images of global conflict like pollution, genocide, and terrorism.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newswire.ca/news-releases/canada-makes-international-design-news-with-launch-of-edit-expo-for-design-innovation--technology-621214063.html|title=Canada Makes International Design News with Launch of EDIT: Expo for Design, Innovation & Technology|website=www.newswire.ca|language=en|access-date=2018-01-29}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category inline|Design Exchange}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20130726110913/http://www.dx.org/ Design Exchange]\n*[http://www.azuremagazine.com/article/bruce-mau-design-solutions-world-problems/ Bruce Mau on How Design Can Solve the World\u2019s Biggest Problems]\n*[http://www.azuremagazine.com/events/edit/ EDIT: Expo for Design, Innovation & Technology]\n*[https://www.canadianarchitect.com/events/edit-expo-design-innovation-technology/ EDIT I Expo for Design, Innovation and Technology]\n*[https://www.canadianinteriors.com/exhibition/dx-design-exchange-festival/1003740460/ Design Exchange launches 10-day biennial festival addressing global challenges]\n*[https://www.insidetoronto.com/news-story/7295479-edit-expo-brings-innovation-to-toronto-s-studio-district/ EDIT expo brings innovation to Toronto's Studio District]\n*[https://news.ontario.ca/mtc/en/2017/01/celebrate-ontarios-150th-anniversary-in-2017.html/ Celebrate Ontario's 150th Anniversary in 2017 Events Taking Place Across the Province Year-Round]\n*[https://nowtoronto.com/news/think-free-blog/prepare-to-party-at-the-old-unilever-soap-factory/ The old Unilever soap factory is open for business]\n*[http://nuvomagazine.com/design/edit-toronto/ EDIT TORONTO Canada\u2019s new immersive design festival.]\n*[https://passport2017.ca/events/edit-expo-design-innovation-technology/ EDIT: Expo for Design, Innovation & Technology]\n*[https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/art-and-architecture/torontos-edit-exhibition-strives-to-serve-global-goals-through-design/article34915374/ Toronto\u2019s EDIT exhibition strives to serve global goals through design]\n*[https://www.theglobeandmail.com/life/home-and-garden/design/bruce-ma